<p>The itemized deduction items:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Mortgage and home equity interests <a href="https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1098.pdf">Form 1098</a>.</li>
  <li>Closing documents if in the year you bought, sold, or re-financed your home or other real estate (<a href="https://files.consumerfinance.gov/f/201311_cfpb_kbyo_closing-disclosure.pdf">Closing disclosure</a>, <a href="https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1099s.pdf">1099-S</a>).</li>
  <li>Real Estate Tax, most likely on <a href="https://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f1098.pdf">Form 1098</a> as well.</li>
  <li>Energy property based on manufacturerâ€™s certification document.</li>
  <li>Personal Property Tax (car tax). In California, vehicle <a href="https://lao.ca.gov/1998/061798_vlf_primer/061798_vlf.html">license fee</a> is deductible, use <a href="https://www.dmv.ca.gov/wasapp/FeeCalculatorWeb/vlfForm.do">this page</a> to find the vehicle license fee. In most major metropolitan areas of Pierce, King, and Snohomish counties of Washington state, Regional Transit Authority tax <a href="https://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/rainier-vehicle-and-vessel-licensing-seattle?select=ALoVRzNvpNoJxOdA_zJiow">(RTA excise tax)</a> is deductible.</li>
  <li>Gifts to charity (cash and non-cash).</li>
  <li>Un-reimbursement expenses related to volunteer work.</li>
  <li>Investment interest (margin interest).</li>
  <li>Medical expenses (prescription, insurance premiums, 
     medical supplies, eye exams, glasses, contacts, co-pays,
     medical transportation (miles), other) above 7.5% of your
     adjusted gross income.</li>
  <li>Long term care insurance premium.</li>
</ul>

